# E-Commerce — Data Model

## Entities

### Entity: Product

An item available for purchase.

```yaml
entity: Product
type: entity
properties:
  id:
    type: string
    required: true
  name:
    type: string
    required: true
  price_cents:
    type: number
    required: true
  inventory:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 0
states: [draft, published, archived, out_of_stock]
lifecycle: draft → published → out_of_stock → archived
```

### Entity: Order

A completed purchase.

```yaml
entity: Order
type: entity
properties:
  id:
    type: string
    required: true
  total_cents:
    type: number
    required: true
  customer_email:
    type: string
    required: true
states: [pending, confirmed, shipped, delivered, refunded]
lifecycle: pending → confirmed → shipped → delivered
```

### Relationship: Order → Product

```yaml
relationship: Order → Product
verb: contains
cardinality: N:N
required: true
```
